115 std::array<double, 6> EstimateFLA::calculate() {
119  int const pole = (Poles(motorRPM, lineFrequency).calculate() / 2) - 1;
120 
124  double const basicFLAValue = motorRatedPower
125  * (flaBasic[0][pole] + (flaBasic[1][pole] * std::exp(-flaBasic[2][pole] * motorRatedPower))
126  + (flaBasic[3][pole] * std::exp(-flaBasic[4][pole] * motorRatedPower)));
130  double const eeMultiplier = eeFlaMultipliers[0][pole]
131  + (eeFlaMultipliers[1][pole] * std::exp(-eeFlaMultipliers[2][pole] * motorRatedPower))
132  + (eeFlaMultipliers[3][pole] * std::exp(-eeFlaMultipliers[4][pole] * motorRatedPower));
136  double const seMultiplier = seFlaMultipliers[0][pole]
137  + (seFlaMultipliers[1][pole] * std::exp(-seFlaMultipliers[2][pole] * motorRatedPower))
138  + (seFlaMultipliers[3][pole] * std::exp(-seFlaMultipliers[4][pole] * motorRatedPower));
139 
143  double const eeFLAValue = eeMultiplier * basicFLAValue;
144  double const seFLAValue = seMultiplier * basicFLAValue;
145 
146  /*
147  * Part load coefficients, 2004
148  * Select partial load multipliers based on pole.
149  */
150  const std::array<std::array<double, 6>, 5> partialLoadCoefficients = calculatePartialLoadCoefficients(pole);
151 
155  auto const plMult = [&partialLoadCoefficients, this] (std::size_t i) {
156  return partialLoadCoefficients[0][i] + (partialLoadCoefficients[1][i] * std::exp(-1 * partialLoadCoefficients[2][i] * motorRatedPower))
157  + (partialLoadCoefficients[3][i] * std::exp(-1 * partialLoadCoefficients[4][i] * motorRatedPower));
158  };
159 
160  const std::array<double, 6> plMultiplier = {
161  {
162  plMult(0), plMult(1), plMult(2), plMult(3), plMult(4), plMult(5)
163  }
164  };
165 
166  // used to calculate FLA
167  auto const adjustForVoltage = [this] (double plVal, double effVal = 0) {
168  auto const estimate = plVal * 460 / ratedVoltage;
169  if (efficiencyClass == Motor::EfficiencyClass::SPECIFIED) {
170  return effVal * estimate * 100 / specifiedEfficiency;
171  }
172  return estimate;
173  };
174 
175  if (efficiencyClass == Motor::EfficiencyClass::PREMIUM) {
176  double const peMultiplier = peFlaMultipliers[0][pole]
177  + (peFlaMultipliers[1][pole] * std::exp(-peFlaMultipliers[2][pole] * motorRatedPower))
178  + (peFlaMultipliers[3][pole] * std::exp(-peFlaMultipliers[4][pole] * motorRatedPower));
179 
180  double const peFLAValue = peMultiplier * basicFLAValue;
181  estimatedFLA = adjustForVoltage(peFLAValue * plMultiplier[4]);
182  return {
183  {
184  peFLAValue * plMultiplier[0], peFLAValue * plMultiplier[1], peFLAValue * plMultiplier[2],
185  peFLAValue * plMultiplier[3], peFLAValue * plMultiplier[4], peFLAValue * plMultiplier[5]
186  }
187  };

206  return {
207  {
208  eeFLAValue * plMultiplier[0], eeFLAValue * plMultiplier[1], eeFLAValue * plMultiplier[2],
209  eeFLAValue * plMultiplier[3], eeFLAValue * plMultiplier[4], eeFLAValue * plMultiplier[5]
210  }
211  };
212  } else if (efficiencyClass == Motor::EfficiencyClass::STANDARD) {
213  estimatedFLA = adjustForVoltage(seFLAValue * plMultiplier[4]);
214  return {
215  {
216  seFLAValue * plMultiplier[0], seFLAValue * plMultiplier[1], seFLAValue * plMultiplier[2],
217  seFLAValue * plMultiplier[3], seFLAValue * plMultiplier[4], seFLAValue * plMultiplier[5]
218  }
219  };
220  } else if (efficiencyClass == Motor::EfficiencyClass::SPECIFIED) {
228 // specifiedEfficiency = 95; // commented out due to this not making sense
229  if (std::fabs(eeFLAValue * plMultiplier[4] - specifiedEfficiency) > std::fabs(seFLAValue * plMultiplier[4] - specifiedEfficiency))
230  {
231  // SE is the nominal efficiency
232  auto const effVal = MotorEfficiency(lineFrequency, motorRPM, Motor::EfficiencyClass::STANDARD,
233  motorRatedPower).calculate(1, specifiedEfficiency);
234  estimatedFLA = adjustForVoltage(seFLAValue * plMultiplier[4], effVal);
235  return {
236  {
237  seFLAValue * plMultiplier[0], seFLAValue * plMultiplier[1], seFLAValue * plMultiplier[2],
238  seFLAValue * plMultiplier[3], seFLAValue * plMultiplier[4], seFLAValue * plMultiplier[5]
239  }
240  };
241  } else {
243  auto const effVal = MotorEfficiency(lineFrequency, motorRPM, Motor::EfficiencyClass::ENERGY_EFFICIENT,
244  motorRatedPower).calculate(1, specifiedEfficiency);
245  estimatedFLA = adjustForVoltage(eeFLAValue * plMultiplier[4], effVal);
246  return {
247  {
248  eeFLAValue * plMultiplier[0], eeFLAValue * plMultiplier[1], eeFLAValue * plMultiplier[2],
249  eeFLAValue * plMultiplier[3], eeFLAValue * plMultiplier[4], eeFLAValue * plMultiplier[5]
250  }
251  };
252  }
253  }
254  return {};
